- Trial phases are stages in a research or experimental process; 
- Data points refer to individual units of data collected during these trials; 
- Access sessions represent periods when data is retrieved or manipulated; 
- Average access duration indicates the typical length of these sessions; 
- The ranking is based on the number of data points accessed and the average duration of access sessions.

